Animal rescue and rehabilitation has always been an integral part of what SeaWorld is. In 2023, our incredible SeaWorld Rescue team has rescued over 80 animals. We have returned 70% back to their natural habitat and working diligently to reach 100%. To date we have rescued over 40,000 animals and are one of the world's largest marine animal rescue organizations. Our teams are on call 24/7/365, partnering with multiple government agencies to rescue and help animals in need of our care! We want to thank our incredible teams for making this possible in 2023. Looking forward to another amazing year!

As this roller coaster of a year comes to a thrilling close, let's loop through the high moments we’ll not soon forget! 🎢🎉Cheers to a New Year we hope will be filled with more smiles, laughs and memory-making! 🥂🌟

As we close out 2023, we want to take a moment to thank the many ambassadors who make up our team here at SeaWorld. ​

​Between last summer's grand opening of Arctic Rescue, an all-new lineup of summer entertainment, the opening of Rescue Jr. and the hatching of our first emperor penguin chick in over a decade, it has been a busy year for all of us! It is because of our team that we can give exceptional care to our animals and deliver one-of-a-kind experiences for our guests all year long. Thank you for an incredible year!

O Playland é tudo de bom!

🚗🚇🚌 - Acesso:  localizado nos principais shoppings em São Paulo e na Bahia, no site (link no perfil) você encontra o endereço de todas as nossas unidades. Algumas ficam do lado de estações do metrô ou trem e todas tem fácil acesso!

☀🌧 - Faça chuva ou faça sol: os Playlands são totalmente cobertos e com ar-condicionado, você aproveita mesmo se o clima lá fora estiver ruim.

🤑 - Passeio democrático: a entrada no Playland é grátis! E você só paga pelas atrações que quiser utilizar. No Caixa ou no Playmania você encontra diversos combos promocionais para aproveitar ainda mais.

🎠 - Atrações: todo mundo se diverte aqui, tem atrações para todos os gostos! E a maioria permite que pais e filhos brinquem juntos.

🕹 - Jogos: além das atrações, um mix completo de jogos de habilidade e competição está disponível, a galera se diverte de montão!

🎟 - Tickets: você sabia que a maioria dos jogos liberam tickets? É isso mesmo! Conforme a sua pontuação você acumula tickets que podem ser trocados por prêmios. É brincar, juntar e trocar!

🎈 - Festas: aqui é o lugar ideal para comemorar o seu aniversário. São vários salões de festas exclusivos que podem ser locados para a sua comemoração ser ainda mais divertida. (para mais informações acesse o site com o link do meu perfil e clique em 'faça sua festa').

- Olha quantos motivos para você vir brincar! Tô te esperando hein!?

Carrossel ou Auto Pista? 🤔

Carrossel 🎠
Um passeio a bordo de cavalinhos que giram e giram ao som de música instrumental e de um visual encantador, repleto de luzes e cores que enchem os olhos!

Auto Pista 🚘
Aperte os cintos e divirta-se pilotando carrinhos de variadas cores sem se preocupar com as batidas! (Se bater a brincadeira fica ainda mais legal).

Essas duas atrações fazem muito sucesso entre as crianças! Que tal chamar os pequenos para vir brincar no Play!? 😁

- A atração 'Carrossel' está disponível em todas as nossas unidades! Já a Auto Pista faz a alegria da garotada em todos os Playlands, exceto: Eldorado e Tatuapé.

- Confira na entrada da atração a altura para acesso e as demais restrições e orientações de segurança. 🤓

It’s time for another quiz!
 
Honu have a remarkable ability called natal homing. This means they can navigate back to the exact beach where they were born when it's time for them to lay their own eggs! Can you guess how they do it?
 
A) They use their keen sense of smell to detect unique scents in the sand.
B) They follow the Earth's magnetic field, like a built-in compass.
C) They communicate with other turtles through secret signals.
D) They memorize the patterns of ocean currents
 
Leave your guess in the comments 💬

'The original 1955 Santa's Village theme park in Skyforest, California was the ultimate expression of mid-century holiday whimsy. There was a candy kitchen, a crooked treehouse, a castle by a 'silver slipper lake', and a little mill with a splashing waterwheel—all with pitched roofs, fanciful trims and inexplicable chimneys. The whole place was like the colourful illustrations in a Whitman storybook had sprung to life. Our favourite building was Santa's Home with a golden 'month clock' and aquamarine A-frame. For Christmas, we made a miniature toy of Santa's house out of wood and metal, and decorated it with vintage bottle brush trees and white sand 'snow'. Should we make the entire Santa's Village??'

THANK YOU to the talented @kevinandjody for sharing this incredible replica of Santa's House from years past! This hits us with all the nostalgic feels on this Christmas Eve. 🥰 Scroll through to see the attention to detail and the 'before' vs 'after'!

What do you all think - should @kevinandjody make the entire Santa's Village? Our vote is YES! ❤

Who doesn't love a good Christmas tree? And you'll find plenty throughout the park when you visit Santa's Village. Did you know...

• The tradition of the Christmas tree was introduced to the United States by German immigrants in the 1700s. However, it wasn't widely popularized until the mid-19th century.
• The smell of a Christmas tree isn't just for ambiance - it's also a stress reliever. The scent of pine has been shown to reduce stress and anxiety. 
• The first Christmas tree lights were lit with candles. Edward H. Johnson, an associate of Thomas Edison, was the first to use electric lights on a Christmas tree in 1882.
• Approximately 80% of American households put up artificial Christmas trees, while the rest opt for real trees. Which type of household are you?
• Some families choose to buy living Christmas trees in pots, which can be planted outdoors after the holiday season. This sustainable practice helps preserve the environment.
• The smallest living Christmas tree on record measured just 1.5 inches tall. It was a Charlie Brown Christmas tree, similar to the iconic one in the Peanuts cartoon.

Embracing the chill on this first day of winter with our cold-weathered friends! Read below for some of their *cool* adaptations. 
❄️ Penguins' waterproof feathers keep them warm and dry in icy waters. Their black and white coloration also serves as camouflage, helping them evade predators and catch prey.
❄️ Walruses have long, sensitive whiskers called vibrissae. These facial bristles help them detect the subtle movements of prey in dark and murky waters. The sensitivity of their vibrissae is a crucial adaptation for locating food in the challenging conditions of the Arctic and subarctic regions.
❄️ A thick layer of blubber insulates harbor seals, reducing heat loss. The blubber of a northern Pacific harbor seal during winter may account for 27-30% of its total body mass!

⁠
'Santa’s Village predates Disneyland by about six weeks, opening on Memorial Day weekend 1955. It was an instant hit, a roadside-style attraction that had grand amusement park ambitions. The Times reported in 1956 that Santa’s Village drew tens of thousands of visitors to the small mountain town in its first year and a half of operation.'⁠

SeaWorld San Diego is heartbroken to share that Ferdinand, a beloved beluga whale, has died at approximately 53 years of age. Ferdinand will be remembered for his great personality and amazing relationships with his animal care team. Ferdinand came to our park in 2004 from Duisberg Zoo in Germany. We are grateful for the time we had with him at SeaWorld San Diego and the positive impact he had on park guests. What we have learned from him has enhanced our understanding of how we can all support the conservation of beluga whales in the wild.

We will miss Ferdinand dearly and we sincerely appreciate the support from our community and his fans all over the world.

At approximately 53 years old, Ferdinand had lived a very full life. Most references for wild beluga whales indicate their lifespan ranges from 30-50 years.

Glenwood Caverns and Iron Mountain Hot Springs were designated as a National Natural Landmark this week! The caves were 2.5 million years in the making, a result of the geologic activity of the hot springs. The two natural wonders are intimately connected, and now they’ll have this special designation in perpetuity. Thank you Interior Secretary Deb Haaland for making it official!

#GlenwoodCavernsAdventurePark #glenwoodsprings #visitcolorado #visitglenwood

The airports always get a little busier this time of year, but this past weekend, there was an extra special passenger arriving. Initially rescued while cold stunned on November 19 by the team at Oregon Coast Aquarium , this Olive Ridley sea turtle was quickly nicknamed 'Sir Acha' since his behavior was described as 'spicy'.​

This past Saturday, December 9, Sir Acha was flown down to San Diego thanks to the help of Turtles Fly Too  and is now receiving continued rehabilitation from the team at SeaWorld Rescue. Upon a successful rehabilitation, he will be returned to the ocean where the water is warmer.

Not only is the buying and selling of many exotic pets illegal, but the trade can lead to diseases that can be transmitted to humans or other animals. Wildlife trafficking and zoonotic diseases are complex, global problems and can feel overwhelming when you don’t know how to help or where to start. Visit notapet.net to learn more and find actions you can take to help.

MOTIVOS PARA VOCÊ VIR BRINCAR:

🚗🚇🚌 - Acesso: estou localizado nos principais shoppings em São Paulo e na Bahia, no meu site (link no perfil) você encontra o endereço de todas as minhas unidades. Algumas ficam do lado de estações do metrô ou trem e todas tem fácil acesso!

☀🌧 - Faça chuva ou faça sol: meus Parques são totalmente cobertos e com ar-condicionado, você aproveita mesmo se o clima lá fora estiver ruim.

🤑 - Passeio democrático: a entrada no Playland é grátis! E você só paga pelas atrações que quiser utilizar. No meu Caixa ou no Playmania você encontra diversos combos promocionais para aproveitar ainda mais.

🎠 - Atrações: todo mundo se diverte aqui, tem atrações para todos os gostos! E a maioria permite que pais e filhos brinquem juntos.

🕹 - Jogos: além das atrações, também ofereço dezenas de jogos de habilidade e competição, a galera se diverte de montão!

🎟 - Tickets: você sabia que a maioria dos jogos liberam tickets? É isso mesmo! Conforme a sua pontuação você acumula tickets que podem ser trocados por prêmios. É brincar, juntar e trocar!

🎈 - Festas: aqui é o lugar ideal para comemorar o seu aniversário. Tenho vários salões de festas exclusivos que podem ser locados para a sua comemoração ser ainda mais divertida. (para mais informações acesse o site com o link do meu perfil e clique em 'faça sua festa').

- Olha quantos motivos para você vir brincar! Tô te esperando hein!?

Often thought of as the most intimate and memorable experience at Santa's Village is our extremely popular 'Tea With Mrs. Claus'. Join the delightful Mrs. Claus and her Elf friends in her special dining room inside the Sky Trading Company.⁠ ☕️🤶🏼
⁠
During the holiday season, enjoy a lovely, unique afternoon of tea, stories, and conversation! Mrs. Claus will teach children of all ages about tea etiquette and will serve a variety of teas and yummy treats. Enjoy delicious scones, finger sandwiches, and sweet little cakes. Only the best tea cups and teapots for her guests on this special occasion! Mrs. Claus always welcomes guests and loves to read them stories, so bring your holiday spirit and join the best tea party in town!

Select dates are still open post-Christmas through January 7th, 2024. Limited seats are available, so don't wait to purchase your Tea and Day Pass tickets (both required) to tell Mrs. Claus all about your holiday!

To close out Walrus Awareness Week, we're excited to share some of the incredible research and partnerships our team and walruses have contributed to, including a hearing study to measure the impacts of white noise with UCSC Oceans Initiative , a partnership with Marine Mammal Institute - Oregon State University to learn about the growth rates of vibrissae and how those can determine previous life events, and lastly providing measurements of healthy walruses to aid U.S. Geological Survey (USGS)  in comparing overhead drone angles.​

​We hope you have enjoyed learning a bit about these amazing animals as much as we have enjoyed sharing them with you. To see more Dozer, Kulu, Basa & Chou Chou be sure to visit us here at SeaWorld San Diego!

We are happy to report that Clarity arrived safely on Dec. 5 from the Miami Seaquarium and is resting comfortably in our medical pool with other manatees as she receives around the clock care and a complete workup by our veterinary and manatee specialist care team. She is in critical but stable condition and while we don’t yet have a complete picture of her current health, we are cautiously optimistic about her future.  We have more than 50 years of manatee care experience and our compassionate and dedicated team will do everything we can to help her return to optimal health at which time wildlife authorities will review her case and determine best placement for her at another facility.  

At the request of the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service, and with the support of the Florida Fish and Wildlife Conservation Commission (FWC) and other members of the Manatee Rescue & Rehabilitation Partnership, SeaWorld safely removed the female manatee Clarity from Miami Seaquarium yesterday. She was transported to SeaWorld Orlando which has one of the largest critical care facilities for manatees in the country. This operation was deemed necessary by authorities for her long-term welfare and is a result of months of careful planning and preparation with various wildlife agencies.

Sensational Seniors is Happy Hollow's monthly program for adults 50+. Join us every second Thursday of the month for mini-walking tours, animal encounters, crafts, activities and a light breakfast! 

This month's theme is 'On a Zoo Diet' Here is where we discuss why meat-eaters are carnivores and why vegetarians are herbivores. Zoo animal diets are prepared in a kitchen just as they would be in a fine dining restaurant. Come to the kitchen with us as we explore the precise science of critter cuisine. Pre-registration is required. More info and registration link at happyhollow.org/hh-experience-programs

It's officially Walrus Awareness Week!
 
As part of the Walrus Conservation Consortium (WCC), we love this opportunity to share a bit about the amazing pinnipeds in our care, their incredible adaptations, and how the studies we've been able to participate and collaborate on with various researchers are helping walruses in the wild.
 
To kick things off, let's take a moment to meet the SeaWorld San Diego walruses- Dozer, Chou Chou, Basa, & Kulu!

Today is International Jaguar Day and World Anteater Day! It just so happens that Happy Hollow has both these animals! Which one is your favorite to visit at the zoo: Sophia the jaguar or Xena and Xander the giant anteaters? 💛🖤

Jaguars are an AZA SAFE (Saving Animals From Extinction) program species, which means that AZA member institutions are working alongside each other and with partner organizations in the field to help save jaguars from extinction. Since the mid-1980s, AZA member institutions have been funding, conducting and supporting jaguar-related fieldwork in Central and South America, including Happy Hollow conservation partners such as the Kaminando Habitat Connectivity Initiative and the Society for the Preservation of Endangered Carnivores and their International Ecological Study (S.P.E.C.I.E.S.) Chaco Jaguar Project. #AZASafeChallenge #SavingSpecies

⛸️ Glide on our frosty dance floor at WinterFest - aka our skating rink! ⛸️ 
 
Snow Flake Lake is located in front of the iconic Wonder Mountain and is the perfect holiday activity for guests of all ages. If you’re interested in ice skating, here’s how:
 
1. Before coming to the park, make a reservation online and select a 30-minute window on your date of choice. https://bit.ly/40YfXLf $15 per guest with rentals, or $10 if you bring your own skates.
2. Sign the online waiver.
3. Once at the park, head over to the Reservation Check-In to redeem your e-ticket skate voucher and get a wristband. Check-in is located on International Street by Yuletide Gift Boutique.
4. At least 15 minutes before your skate time, if you’re renting skates, head to the Skate Rental Shop. If you’re not renting, take your skates to the lace up area. 
5. And now you’re ready to head to Snow Flake Lake to skate! Enjoy!!! ❄️

Leaf piles are tons of fun for Happy Hollow's animals to play in, and they can also be beneficial to the environment 🍁 When you choose to #LeaveTheLeaves, you are supporting local pollinators! 🦋 Some butterflies, for instance, use fallen leaves as cover in the winter, providing protection from cold weather and predators.  As a bonus, throughout the season, leaves will decompose and bring nutrients to your soil. So instead of bagging the leaves in your yard, consider leaving them out or raking them off to the side and leaving the pile 🍂 
📸: Keeper Elissa

Happy Hollow's parrots love tearing up newspaper for enrichment 🦜Sometimes parrots rip up paper due to their natural nesting instincts, using the material to create nests for chicks. In the case of Happy Hollow's macaws, they like to use their beaks to explore their surroundings, and tearing up paper and cardboard also helps them maintain nice and healthy beaks 💛

📸: Keeper Elissa

Imagine select Cedar Fair parks as your learning lab and Bowling Green State University as your classroom. Earn a degree in Resort and Attraction Management! 🎢 Learn more - https://bit.ly/CFBGSU

Season Pass vs. Gold Pass

What's the difference? The only difference between a Season Pass and a Gold Pass is that a Gold Pass allows for the pass holder to bring 2 additional guests into the park each day they visit. The Season Pass is only valid for the pass holder. 

Which one is right for you? If the same people will always be coming to the park together, then a regular Season Pass is probably the right way to go. However, if the pass holder likes to bring different people during their visit, or they want more flexibility, then a Gold Pass is probably more suitable.

Can I put the Gold Pass in my child's name? Absolutely! We have a lot of guests who put a Gold Pass in their child's name so grandma and grandpa, or an aunt and uncle can take them. The only requirement is that the pass holder must be present.

Weather Update for Monday 11/20
We are experiencing high winds and blowing snow. Snow is expected to continue all day so we will not be able to operate our rides today. We will open our Village today from 9:30-2pm so that our guests and Santa's helpers can get home safe during daytime hours. Santa will be available to visit and our village shops will be open, and our magic show will be available. So if you want to see the snowy village and visit Santa and take in a magic show you can do that for free today. From 9:30am-2pm. 
If you have an online ticket and we haven't already rescheduled you or processed the refund and you would still like to visit the park today we will refund your tickets at the gate or If you would not like to visit today and have an online ticket give us a call and we will process that refund.

Santa’s Workshop & Post Office is one of Santa’s favorite places in the park, where he crafts all the presents and imagines the joy on children’s faces when they unwrap the gifts on Christmas morning. You can even join the Elves and create your very own Christmas ornament or toy during your visit to Santa's Village.⁠
⁠
And don’t forget to write your own letter! Santa loves getting mail, so decorate your list for him or send a thank-you note for the presents you received last year.⁠
⁠
PRO TIP: Santa's Workshop is very popular during the holiday season. We recommend stopping by earlier in your day to make sure your elf experience is complete and you get the toy selection of your choice!*⁠
⁠
At Santa’s Workshop & Post Office, the spirit of Christmas comes alive, one festive creation and heartfelt letter at a time! ⁠
⁠
*Additional fee applies for optional toy decorating as you get to take your creation home with you! And if you've upgraded to our Christmas VIP Experience, toy decorating is included with Admission (don't forget to bring your coupons)! 🎅🏼🎄⭐️

Santa's Village Insider Secrets: Unwrap the Magic with These Jolly Tips for Your Christmas Adventure! 🎅✨⁠
⁠
FAQs⁠
1. Can I purchase tickets at the door?⁠
We strongly recommend purchasing your tickets online in advance. The holiday season is the busiest time of the year at Santa’s Village and, as a result, tickets will sell out. Same-day tickets are not guaranteed. Plus, you'll receive the best rate when pre-purchasing tickets online vs at the door. Please note that paid admission and waivers are required for all guests entering Santa’s Village, regardless of participation in activities.⁠
⁠
2. How do I visit Santa?⁠
To visit Santa during the holiday season, you will need to make a reservation the day of your visit. Once you arrive at the park and get checked in, head to Santa’s House to speak to one of our elves who will walk you through the process. ⁠All reservations to see Santa must be made in person and on a first-come, first-served basis. There are a limited number of reservations per day and once they are filled, guests will be asked to wait in the Standby Line. Please note that visits with Santa are not guaranteed, so arriving at 10am when the park opens will give the best opportunity to visit with him. While we do our best to accommodate all guests in the Standby Line, the sheer volume of visitors means that Santa doesn’t always get to see everyone.⁠
⁠
3. Will there be snow, and do I need chains?⁠
Santa’s Village does not create artificial snow. While there may be snow during your visit, it is entirely dependent on Mother Nature. We cannot predict or promise any particular weather. Be aware that icy road conditions may exist in the mountains during the cold months, and only drive when it is safe to do so. ⁠All vehicles need to carry chains when heading to the mountains during the winter months. Please check the weather in Skyforest before making your travel plans and refer to CalTrans for up-to-date road conditions.

Earlier this week, we announced cornerstone investments in the preservation of manatees and Guadalupe fur seals, committing up to $1.075 million over up to four years through the SeaWorld Conservation Fund. The initial investments encompass three organizations and will help support vital census work and tagging for imperiled Gudalupe fur seals, along with habitat restoration, rescue, rehabilitation, release, monitoring and education for manatees globally. It will also help make possible the building of the first African manatee rehabilitation center in Cameroon. 

The investments are part of a new strategy to drive greater impact among species of concern. Over the next several years, the Fund will work closely with these organizations as they make a positive impact on our planet's endangered species. In addition to support through the Fund, SeaWorld parks help manatee and Guadalupe fur seal conservation with rescue, rehabilitation, and return. Learn more: https://bit.ly/3MKK9Dw

To experience the magic of meeting Santa during our holiday season, secure your spot by making a reservation the day of your visit. Once you've arrived at the park and are checked in, make your way to Santa's House, where one of Santa's helpful elves will guide you through the experience! 🎁🎅⁠🎄✨⁠
⁠
Reservations with Santa are made in person and are granted on a first-come, first-served basis. There are a limited number of reservations available each day. So once they're filled, guests have the option to join the Standby Line for a chance to meet the big man himself.
⁠
Please keep in mind, while we wish Santa could meet every single visitor, the North Pole is bustling with excitement, and visits aren't guaranteed. We truly do our best to sprinkle holiday joy to everyone waiting in the Standby Line, but the overwhelming number of visitors to our Christmas village means that Santa might not get to see everyone. ⁠Arriving when the park opens at 10am will give guests the best opportunity to secure their reservation before it gets busy!
⁠

For more information click here: https://skyparksantasvillage.com/parks/santas-village/

Today we remember and honour members of the armed forces who lost their lives in the line of duty. Lest we forget.

Today, and every day, we are grateful for our military personnel, past and present, and the families who support them. To those who courageously gave their lives and those who bravely fight today, thank you for your service, sacrifice and dedication. I know this is a 24/7 job and protecting our country and freedom doesn’t come easy. Thinking of you on Veterans Day and thanking you for all you did for the greatest country in the world. 

This is my prayer for you today:

Father,
Please turn your thoughts to those men and women who in their military service have sacrificed time, comfort, strength, ambition, health and prosperity for the peace and safety of family and friends and others they’ve never even known. Please reward them a hundredfold for all their sacrifice and service. Bless them far beyond all their expectations. Reward them richly for all they have given. Provide them with good health as the walk their path on earth. Thank you for all you have giving us and God Bless America. Amen

Gratefully,
 
John Arie Jr
Chief Executive Officer
Fun Spot America Theme Parks
Today and every day, we salute Service Members both past and present. We are grateful for everything they have done to protect us.
This Veterans Day, we'd like to take a moment to honor members of our U.S. Armed Forces, past and present. From all of us at the Disneyland Resort, thank you for your selfless service. 🇺🇸

To our Veterans Jim, Mike, Robert, Jarrell, Shelley, Jeremy, Johnnie and Robert, today we honor you and everything you have done for our country.

THANK YOU to all of those who have served, are still serving and the families of our Veterans.

The votes have been tallied (over 29,000 of them!) and we have an official name for our Emperor penguin chick!​

​We are so proud to officially introduce you all to sweet little Pearl! Thank you to everyone who helped us in choosing her name, and we think it fits our small (for now) but steadily growing, precious little chick beautifully.​

You're invited! 🐆 Join Cheetah Conservation Fund and Happy Hollow Park & Zoo on Saturday, November 11, for a paint & sip event at Narrative Fermentations, benefitting cheetah conservation. Learn about the plight of the cheetah, and how CCF has created holistic methods to reduce their extinction, from CCF's founder and executive director, Dr. Laurie Marker. Then enjoy a watercolor lesson from local artist Elvira Rascov, who will walk you step by step through creating your own cheetah greeting cards. No previous art experience required. Drinks and food will be available for purchase, and you'll get $1 off your first drink with your event ticket purchase. Space is limited, so grab your ticket now to ensure your spot! 🎨 Tickets can be purchased at https://cheetah.org/events/paint-night-at-narrative-fermentations-san-jose-ca/ 🖌️

Are you missing Senior Safari? Check out Sensational Seniors! The Happy Hollow Zoo Education team hosts Sensational Seniors for adults 50+ from November to April, during the Senior Safari off-season. This program allows seniors to continue to gather with fellow zoo lovers to learn about the various aspects of animal care, husbandry and conservation. Please note that pre-registration is required for Sensational Seniors.

The first Sensational Seniors of the season will be Thursday, November 16 from 9 to 10:30 a.m. This session's topic will be Animal Acquisition, where attendees can learn where zoo animals come from and what it takes to transfer animals between facilities. For this first program of the season, register by reaching out to the Zoo Education team by phone at 408-794-6420 or by email at hhpzeducation@sanjoseca.gov.

Sophia the jaguar turned 20 years old over the weekend! 🐆 The median life expectancy of a jaguar at an AZA zoo is 18 years, but Sophia is still in great health 💛 It's not unusual for Happy Hollow's animals to live well past their life expectancy due to the excellent care they receive from zoo staff. On your next Happy Hollow visit, stop by the Zoo in the Hollow and catch Sophia snoozing, rolling around in the grass, or trying to eat you from the other side of the glass 😅

📸: Keepers Elissa, Veronica, and Sammy

It's National Sandwich Day! 🥪 The sandwich is believed to be the namesake of John Montagu, the 4th Earl of Sandwich, following the claim that he invented the first ever sandwich. As one of America’s most popular lunch items, this day gives us a great reason to enjoy a sandwich at St. Nicks, Billy's BBQ, or the Lunch Box! ⁠

HISTORY OF NATIONAL SANDWICH DAY
Though the combination of bread filled with cheese and meats has been enjoyed for years prior, the creation and naming of the sandwich has been attributed to the 4th Earl of Sandwich, John Montagu. In 1762 the earl, who was fond of gambling, asked his cook to prepare him a meal that wouldn’t require cutlery nor interfere with his 24 hour long gambling streak. The cook gave him sliced meat between two pieces of toast, which allowed the earl to have one hand free to continue his game. 

Of course, neither the earl nor the cook were the actual inventors of the sandwich. It is said that prior to this aforementioned event, Mantagu had visited the Eastern Mediterranean and saw sandwiches served by the Greeks and Turks with their appetizers, and asked his cook to copy their methods for its convenience. By the Revolutionary war a few years later, sandwiches were a well established English meal. However, they didn’t make their way to America until they were included in an American cookbook in 1815.

The New Orlean’s Po’ Boy came around during the Great Depression during a streetcar worker strike. Two brothers who were former streetcar workers owned a sandwich shop and promised to feed any striking worker for free. Whenever a hungry worker would walk over to the shop, the clerks would say “Here comes another po’ boy,” which soon became the name of the sandwich itself. In Omaha, Nebraska, the Reuben made its first appearance. It was named after one of the players of a weekly poker game that took place in a hotel. The hotel owner decided to feature the sandwich on the hotel’s dinner menu and later, it won a nationwide recipe contest.

You're invited!🐆 Join Cheetah Conservation Fund (CCF) and Happy Hollow Park & Zoo for a paint event at Narrative Fermentations, benefitting cheetah conservation. Learn about the plight of the cheetah and how CCF has created holistic methods to reduce their extinction from CCF's founder and executive director, Dr. Laurie Marker. Then enjoy a watercolor lesson from local artist Elvira Rascov of Elvira Gallery, who will walk you step by step through creating your own cheetah greeting cards. No previous art experience required. Drinks and food will be available for purchase, and you'll get $1 off your first drink with your event ticket purchase. Space is limited, so grab your ticket now to ensure your spot! 🎨🖌️

WEATHER ALERT: We woke up to an icy morning here at the North Pole! We are currently working on clearing our paths and rides of ice and the current forecast does predict we'll start getting snow accumulation earlier than expected. Because of this we will be open today with and early closing of 3pm and will have a discounted ride wristband rate of $20 per person instead of the normal $32. Rides will open as soon as we get the paths and platforms cleared of ice. We will be closing at 3pm today due to the weather expected to come in so that we can clear our park of guests and Santa's Helpers before the weather gets too bad to ensure everyone exits the park safely and gets home safely.
Stay safe and warm today!!

As part of Happy Hollow's Green Halloween celebration, the team created an ofrenda in the Zoo on the Hill to honor some of the zoo animals that have passed on. 

Day of the Dead, or Día de Los Muertos, is a celebration of life. It recognizes death as a part of life,  remembering ancestors and loved ones and keeping them alive in our hearts and minds. An ofrenda, meaning “offering” in Spanish, is an altar with items that honor loved ones who have passed away.

Please stop by the ofrenda in front of Doc's Critter Care to honor the Happy Hollow animals we continue to hold in our hearts ❤️

Happy #WorldLemurDay! #DYK: There are over 100 species of lemur, and 98% of them (all but 4 species) are threatened with extinction. How can you help? Make responsible choices as a consumer to lower your carbon footprint and support companies that harvest resources sustainably, learn about lemurs and share what you know with your family and friends, or donate to conservation organizations that work to help lemurs if you are able.  You can find even more great suggestions from Lemur Conservation Network at lemurconservationnetwork.org/how-to-help

Happy Hollow Park & Zoo is home to 3 lemur species: ring-tailed, red ruffed, and black and white ruffed. Be sure to see them all on your next visit! 📹: Keeper Emily

We have an announcement that's both exciting AND adorable! For the first time since 2010, an emperor penguin chick has hatched here at SeaWorld San Diego! Emperor penguins are currently listed as a threatened species under the Endangered Species Act due to the loss of Antarctic sea ice and rising sea levels caused by climate change, and as the only zoo in the Western Hemisphere where emperor penguins can be found, we are excited to share and celebrate this rare and precious emperor penguin chick!​

Hatched on September 12, she enjoys a steady diet of fish and 'fish milkshakes', gaining at a healthy rate of 5%-10% of her body weight per day! Her little chirps have already stolen the hearts of our aviculture team and we can't wait for our guests to enjoy her as well!​

Want to help us name this little one? 🐧 You have through 10/31 to cast your vote for her name at https://bit.ly/3Mg3YT9

Our two toed sloths Tess & Yiscel wish YOU a happy International Sloth Day! 🦥​

​Did you know that sloths are the world's slowest mammal? Their slow movements keep them at an incredibly low metabolic rate, allowing them to conserve energy. However, they are excellent swimmers- traveling three times as fast on water as they do on land!​

​We hope you'll celebrate International Sloth by giving yourself a moment to take things a little slower! Or better yet, book yourself a Sloth Up-Close Encounter and learn from these experts firsthand! Reservations are available at https://bit.ly/4048OZs

5 MOTIVOS PARA VOCÊ NOS VISITAR:

🚗🚇🚌 - Acesso: estou localizado nos principais shoppings em São Paulo e na Bahia, no meu site (link no perfil) você encontra o endereço de todas as minhas unidades. Algumas ficam do lado de estações do metrô ou trem e todas tem fácil acesso!

☀🌧 - Faça chuva ou faça sol: meus Parques são totalmente cobertos e com ar-condicionado, você aproveita mesmo se o clima lá fora estiver ruim.

🤑 - Passeio democrático: a entrada no Playland é grátis! E você só paga pelas atrações que quiser utilizar. No meu Caixa ou no Playmania você encontra diversos combos promocionais para aproveitar ainda mais.

🎠 - Atrações: todo mundo se diverte aqui, tem atrações para todos os gostos! E a maioria permite que pais e filhos brinquem juntos.

🕹 - Jogos: além das atrações, também ofereço dezenas de jogos de habilidade e competição, a galera se diverte de montão!

🎟 - Tickets: você sabia que a maioria dos jogos liberam tickets? É isso mesmo! Conforme a sua pontuação você acumula tickets que podem ser trocados por prêmios. É brincar, juntar e trocar!

🎈 - Festas: aqui é o lugar ideal para comemorar o seu aniversário. Tenho vários salões de festas exclusivos que podem ser locados para a sua comemoração ser ainda mais divertida. (para mais informações acesse o site com o link do meu perfil e clique em 'faça sua festa').

- Olha quantos motivos para você vir brincar! Tô te esperando hein!?

While every SeaWorld Rescue return is special, it is especially meaningful when our team is able to help animals whose species are included in the Endangered Species Act, as was the case for both this Olive Ridley Sea Turtle and Guadalupe Fur Seal.​

Rescued as a pup on April 18 up in Malibu by California Wildlife Center, this Guadalupe Fur Seal was emaciated and lethargic. After being stabilized, she was transported into SeaWorld's care facility on April 21 for continued treatment where our team was able to help her grow to a healthy weight and activity level.​

This Olive Ridley Sea Turtle had an especially long road to recovery, being originally rescued at Horsefall Beach in Coos Bay by the Oregon Coast Aquarium from being 'cold stunned' with a body temperature of 60 degrees nearly a year ago. After being stabilized to a healthy temperature in early November of last year, she was transported to SeaWorld San Diego via the non-profit Turtles Fly Too. With supervision and assistance, the SeaWorld Rescue team was able to help her build up the strength to swim on her own, getting her to a healthy weight and activity level before her successful return this past week.​

​We are proud of this collaboration with California Wildlife Center, Oregon Coast Aquarium, & Turtles Fly Too, and the continued contributions towards these animals whose populations are most vulnerable.​

​Activities conducted under a MMPA/ESA permit authorization and the Stranding Agreement between NMFS and SeaWorld California.

ICYMI: yesterday, we announced a historical milestone in conservation with the birth of three critically endangered sawfish pups! SeaWorld Orlando is the second aquarium in the world to have a successful smalltooth sawfish birth; setting a new standard for expert care and conservation efforts.

The newborns include two females and one male, born on July 11, 2023, and each measured approximately two feet in length. Following their birth, the pups underwent a comprehensive examination, and continue to receive regular check-ups to ensure their sustained health and expected developmental progress. This milestone underscores SeaWorld’s commitment to preserving biodiversity and saving species from extinction.

On Oct 14, African Penguin Awareness Day, we celebrate the biggest-ever worldwide waddle, highlighting the looming extinction of African Penguins. #NotOnOurWatch

Did you know that the African Penguin wild population numbers have dropped by 99% in the last 100 years? In 10 years time, this species will become extinct due to man-made issues including overfishing and pollution. Practicing better waste reduction and being more aware of what seafood (Ocean Wise is the best!) you are purchasing can immensely help to curb this.

Come by Marine Life to learn about these amazing animals today and https://www.africanpenguinnotonourwatch.org/email-the-minister for more information on #NotOnOurWatch.

SeaWorld is part of the Marine Mammal Stranding Network and as a member we work with various agencies across the state. This sea lion was a yearling pup that was treated by The Pacific Marine Mammal Center in Laguna Beach for potentially deadly domoic acid toxicity and returned to the ocean in good health. Unfortunately the sea lion became thin during his journey and had a minor eye injury and stranded again in San Diego. The SeaWorld Rescue Team was called to the rescue and through the network we tracked the sea lion to view his past history. During rehabilitation at SeaWorld, we were able to treat its eye and bring it back to a healthy weight before returning him into the ocean.

TOP 5: As atrações favoritas das crianças! 🤩

Arrasta pro lado <<<<<<<<

O Playland oferece atrações para toda a família curtir, desde opções mais emocionantes, até atrações que fazem a alegria dos pequenos.

- Carrossel: as luzes e as cores dessa atração fazem brilhar os olhos das crianças. É sempre uma boa pedida!

- Kid Play: um percurso cheio de obstáculos, piscina de bolinhas, escorregadores e muito mais!

- Auto Pista: atração clássica onde as crianças podem se sentir verdadeiros pilotos, percorrendo uma pista a bordo de carrinhos coloridos.

- Samba Balloon: balões coloridos que fazem a alegria e a diversão da família inteira, as crianças se esbaldam de brincar!

- Dragon: uma montanha-russa feita especialmente para as crianças, com doses moderadas de emoção e velocidade.

It is with our deepest sorrow that we share the news that we lost our beloved walrus Mitik who had resided at SeaWorld San Diego since 2016. He was found as an orphaned calf in the Arctic in 2012 within weeks of his birth. SeaWorld was asked to send members of our Rescue Team to assist the Alaska SeaLife Center with Mitik’s rehabilitation. Deemed non-releasable by wildlife authorities because at his young age he lacked the skills to survive on his own, Mitik spent time at several aquariums throughout his life. During his time at SeaWorld, Mitik actively contributed to hearing and photogrammetry research, which will benefit the wild walrus population.​

​Mitik was treated intensively the last several weeks for acute kidney disease and despite ongoing medical attention, passed away this weekend. Always by his side was Mitzi Synnott, Zoological Supervisor, who helped care for Mitik since his days of rehabilitation in Alaska.​

​“Working with Mitik in Alaska after his 2012 rescue, as well as being part of his daily animal care team has been the highlight of my 30-year career. There are not enough words to describe how special he was. He was gentle, patient, responsive and created meaningful bonds with his animal care team and veterinarians. I spent years caring for him and I will never forget him.” – Mitzi​

​Mitik will forever be in our hearts. His rescue story is a legacy and will continue to be shared to educate guests about walruses and how important they are and the impacts they face in the wild.

Saiba tudo sobre o cartão queridinho dos Playmaníacos:

- O que é: o Playcard é um cartão exclusivo do Play, com ele você tem acesso a todas as nossas atrações, de forma prática e simples! 😊

- Como funciona: você pode abastecê-lo com créditos, acumular bônus e até os tickets (recebidos durante as partidas em nossos jogos), tudo isso pode ficar registrado em seu Playcard. 🤗

- Para ter o seu: ainda não tem um Playcard? Adquira o seu cartão por apenas R$ 5 direto em nossos caixas!

- Como faz para abastecê-lo? É muito fácil! Você pode aproveitar as promoções do Playmania (o e-commerce do Play) ou utilizar um dos Caixas físicos das nossas unidades, vai ter sempre ofertas e combos especiais para você aproveitar de montão! 🤑

- Tem valor mínimo para recarga? Não! Você pode abastecer o Playcard com quantos créditos quiser.

- E se eu perder o Playcard? Quer uma dica? Acesse agora mesmo o Playmania e associe o seu Playcard ao seu cadastro, dessa maneira, em caso de perda do cartão é possível bloquear e recuperar todo o saldo. 😉

On this #ManedWolfDay, let's celebrate the AZA-accredited organizations providing the gold standard of care to numerous maned wolves at facilities across the world! Did you know these facilities also work to support on-the-ground conservation efforts to protect wild #ManedWolves? The Maned Wolf #SAFE conservation efforts include the rescue, rehabilitation, and repatriation of confiscated and injured wolves. You can help support these efforts by visiting your local AZA organization today!

A premiação é a mais importante do segmento de atendimento do Brasil, reconhecendo através do voto popular as empresas com as melhores reputações do mercado, baseadas na percepção de um atendimento eficaz, cuidadoso e excelente aos consumidores, mesmo quando estes enfrentam contratempos com algum produto ou serviço oferecido pela empresa.

O Playland e o Playcenter Family estão concorrendo na categoria 'Lazer e Entretenimento' e a votação começa hoje e vai até o fim de outubro.

Walt Disney Imagineering & NASA - National Aeronautics and Space Administration combined the magic of space & Disney to update an in-park display recreating the surface of Mars in Mission: SPACE at EPCOT. 🚀

NASA’s Jet Propulsion Laboratory provided images captured by NASA's Perseverance Mars Rover as reference for our artisans, a 3D print file to recreate sample tubes used on Mars, and loaned a prototype wheel of the Perseverance rover to create tread marks identical to those currently on Mars. Perseverance continues its mission on Mars to collect samples that a future mission could one day return to Earth.

Los Angeles-born Milton Quon was a graduate of Chouinard Art Institute (now known as California Institute of the Arts) and joined Disney Animation in 1939, working on films such as Fantasia and Dumbo. After illustrating for Douglas Aircraft throughout World War II, Milton returned to the Studio in 1946 to head up the publicity department.

✨ Join us as we look at the artistry, technology, and people that have shaped #100YearsofDisneyAnimation.

Happy Rock Day!​

Our aviculturists have been busy distributing over 20,000 lbs of river rocks throughout the Penguin Encounter for four species of penguins (macaroni, gentoo, chinstrap and Adélie) to use to build nests. It's an annual tradition we call 'Rock Day' and kicks off the breeding season!​

The rocks, which are also an important part of the penguins' courtship and pair bonding displays, are spread out over nesting areas called rookeries. After rocks are distributed, the penguins will begin to collect them and build nests for their breeding season.​

Be sure to come visit our Penguin Encounter and you just might spy some penguins cozying up in their brand new rock nests thanks to the efforts of the SeaWorld team!

Did you know that the female Hawaiian sea turtle can lay an impressive number of eggs, ranging anywhere from 60 to 120 at a time? Our conservation center exhibit is the perfect place to learn more about their incredible life cycle, the challenges they face, and the important conservation efforts underway. 

Stop by during your next park visit!

As the days grow shorter and the air becomes crisper, we can't help but get excited for what's to come. Join us and embrace the changing seasons with your family at our Pumpkins in the Pines festival! Create cherished memories while picking pumpkins and celebrating the charming beauty of autumn together! 🎃🌲🍁 ⁠
⁠
Pumpkins in the Pines returns to SkyPark at Santa’s Village October 7th-29th. Saturdays and Sundays in October, join us for a parkwide pumpkin patch, trick-or-treating, seasonal food & beverages, costume contests, pumpkin painting, the Magical Pumpkin Meadowlands Train Ride, the Legend of Sleepy Hollow Puppet Show, and towards the end of the month, our newest addition to the festival 'SkyPark After Dark' which includes a chilling walk through our Fantom Forest (stay tuned for more info).⁠
⁠
Celebrate the fall season with family-friendly outdoor activities and abundant photo ops. And don’t forget to stop by Kringle’s Coffee & Gifts for a truly delectable pumpkin spiced latte. ⁠
So, let's embrace this season of transformation and family togetherness, as we welcome the changing leaves and the traditions that come with them. ⁠
⁠
More info on our blog: https://skyparksantasvillage.com/pumpkins-in-the-pines-2023/

Angela shared one of her all-time favorite photos of her grandma, Diana. It was taken in 1960 when she was about 17 years old. Here's the kicker: In this snapshot, Diana is striking a pose with a surfboard, channeling some serious surfer vibes, even though she had never caught a wave in her life! While Instagram wouldn't exist for another 50 years, Diana was already 'doing it for the 'gram.' Talk about being a trendsetter ahead of her time! 🌊🏄🏻‍♀️🏖 #TBT

Happy black-footed ferret rediscovery day! The black-footed ferret was once thought to be extinct, until this day 42 years ago when a small population of them was rediscovered in Wyoming. Since then, zoos and other conservation organizations have made big strides in helping with black-footed ferret conservation, although black-footed ferrets are still an endangered species today. The Association of Zoos and Aquariums Saving Animals from Extinction (SAFE) program is working hard toward recovery of the black-footed ferret such that it no longer meets the Endangered Species Act’s definition of endangered and is downlisted to threatened. Happy Hollow helps educate the public about this unique species with resident education ambassadors, Apollo and Hermes, two domestic ferrets.

Over five decades, Carmen De La Torre Sanderson brought her talents to Disney Animation productions, adapting her skills to new technologies. As an artist in the Ink & Paint department, she painted cels for Make Mine Music (1946), Xeroxed cels for Sleeping Beauty (1959), and digitally painted cels using CAPS (Computer Animation Production System) for Home on the Range (2004).

✨ Join us as we look at the artistry, technology, and people that have shaped #100YearsofDisneyAnimation

We are so excited to announce the success of the Cystic Fibrosis Foundation Walk at the park! 

The mission of the Cystic Fibrosis Foundation is to cure cystic fibrosis and to provide all people with CF the opportunity to lead long, fulfilling lives by funding research and drug development, partnering with the CF community, and advancing high-quality, specialized care.

Thanks to the kind donations and sponsorships of our participants, over $30,000 was raised to help the funding of research to prevent and cure Cystic Fibrosis.

Today marks the official start of Sea Otter Awareness Week!

Aside from being otterly adorable, Southern Sea Otters are a 'Keystone Species' since they play a big part in maintaining sea urchin populations, which are vital for helping kelp forests to thrive! ✨ Not only do kelp forests provide food, nursery areas and shelter for countless species, but they also help combat climate change, ocean acidification and shoreline erosion.

Do your part to protect sea otters by keeping trash and other pollutants out of the ocean and staying 5 kayak lengths away if you see them in the wild. 🌊🦦

Be sure to join us this week to learn more about what makes these animals so special, as well as fun facts about the fabulous Sea Otters you can visit right here at SeaWorld San Diego!

It's #InternationalFerretDay! #DYK that ferrets have a fast metabolism so they eat frequently? This never-ending appetite is one major reason why ferrets are illegal to have as pets in California; if released into the wild, they could eat many of our fantastic native animals. Happy Hollow has a special permit to keep these two as education ambassadors - so we can teach people about responsible pet ownership and about the endangered black-footed ferret that is native to the Great Plains.

Retta Scott was hired in 1939, at the age of 23, to storyboard scenes for Bambi (1942). Working in charcoal, she produced a dramatic scene of Bambi and Faline fighting off a pack of hunting dogs. Impressed by her strong posing and sense of realism, Walt Disney and animator David Hand agreed that Retta should also animate the scenes.

Retta had never animated, but the sense of action and character depicted in her boards made her a natural choice for animator. She drew what she recalled to be “56,000 dogs for Bambi” – animating both rough and clean-up animation - and became the first female animator to receive screen credit.

✨ Join us as we look at the artistry, technology, and people that have shaped #100YearsofDisneyAnimation

#FunFactFriday DID YOU KNOW? The Antique Carousel (The oldest ride at the park) arrived at Lake Winnie in 1968 after originally opening in Atlanta in 1916. With 68 hand-carved, wooden horses, The Antique Carousel at Lake Winnie is among the oldest and largest in the country. Did you know Sesame Street Land at SeaWorld Orlando is a Certified Autism Center™ as designated by our partner, the IBCCES? This certification is an ongoing commitment to serve our community and families with special needs. We are proud to announce that Sesame Street Land at SeaWorld Orlando has recently completed our first staff-wide recertification in 2023.

At a park level, becoming a Certified Autism Center through IBCCES has helped our Ambassadors become better equipped to serve autistic and sensory-sensitive guests.
On a larger level, this certification aligns with Sesame Workshop’s mission to increase public awareness of autism and foster greater empathy and understanding.
We worked closely with IBCCES to have all our attractions audited on a sensory scale to create a branded Sensory Guide for our guests. This guide is available online and at Guest Relations, and guests can find corresponding sensory levels printed on attraction signage in Sesame Street Land. 

Thank you IBCCES for being such an amazing partner, and providing us with the ability to further advance the message of awareness, understanding, and inclusion for everyone.

For more information about this program, IBCCES, and Sesame Street Land at SeaWorld Orlando, visit: https://bit.ly/3t2Tekf

E na recordação de hoje: o DNA - Dia Nacional da Alegria 😊

Essa é uma ação social promovida pelo @Sindepat em parceria com a @AdibraOficial, que conta com a participação do Grupo Playcenter através dos Playlands e do Playcenter Family (@playcenterfamilyoficial).

O DNA é um dia inteiro de alegria e diversão destinado para crianças atendidas por diversas instituições sociais, a iniciativa acontece por aqui e também  em parques e atrações turísticas de todo o Brasil, recebendo milhares de crianças e famílias de maneira gratuita.😄

Este ano o DNA foi comemorado em abril e a data faz parte de uma série de ações realizadas ao longo do ano. Já estamos ansiosos para a próxima edição!

This past Friday the SeaWorld Rescue Team successfully returned three rehabilitated tropicbirds back to their natural habitats.

The red-billed tropicbirds were all blown inland by tropical storm Hurricane Hilary and were found thin and dehydrated when the SeaWorld Rescue Team was called upon. They are a very rare species for San Diego to see as they live at sea except when they nest, and our rescue team has only come across them twice in over 20 years!

Our team was grateful to be able to successfully return them back into their natural habitat.

Kansas City, Missouri, may best be known in animation circles as the childhood home of Walt Disney, but it also helped shape the early life and career of animator Marshall Toomey,  who admits that he followed in Walt’s footsteps unknowingly.

Both men were fascinated with cartoons from an early age and drew constantly. Both had fathers who worked for local newspapers (Walt’s father made him work the paper route while Marshall’s brought home paper for him to draw on). Both attended McKinley High School and art classes at the Kansas City Art Institute. Finally, both got their start creating animation for local advertising companies.

✨ Join us as we look at the artistry, technology, and people that have shaped #100YearsofDisneyAnimation.

Today SeaWorld San Diego had the honor of hosting 6 patients from Rady Children's Hospital @radychildrens for a very special experience with our Dolphin Interaction Program.

The program began in 2007 when Joy Clausen Soto, a SeaWorld dolphin trainer who battled and overcame non-Hodgkin's lymphoma and underwent treatment at Children's Hospital in Southern California, started the program with other zoological team members.

Thank you to the team at Rady Children's Hospital for their incredible work and for the heartfelt reminder of how lucky we are to share the wonder of these animals with the world.

The Northwoods' royal family invites you to try your hand and test your mettle at the Royal Games! Three challenges await would-be knights of the Northwoods:⁠⁠• Princess Evergreen invites you to practice your archery skills at her private outdoor range. Our trained Adventure Crew team members will give you a basic lesson, then send you off to practice.⁠⁠• Test your throwing skills at King Celwyn’s Ax Challenge! Learn the old-world techniques that the Knights of the NorthWoods have known for millennia. And keep an eye out for King Celwyn; he frequently visits to make sure his squires are earning their knighthoods.⁠⁠• No visit to the Royal Games would be complete without stopping by the NorthWoods Sharpshooter Gallery. Guests can take aim and test their skills under the supervision of our trained Adventure Crew team members.⁠⁠Once you've tried your hand at all three, be sure to join King Celwyn at the Royal Knighting Ceremony at 3:30pm each day to earn your badge and bragging rights! Huzzah!

It's International Red Panda Day! ❤️🐼 Do you ever have trouble spotting the red pandas in their habitat at Happy Hollow? Red pandas are covered in thick fur because their natural habitat is very cold ❄️ So on hot days, it's pretty common for them to hang out in their night house where they have air conditioning ☀️ Take a peek inside the window to the side of the habitat and maybe you can spot the red pandas having a snack! 🎍🌱

📸: Krystel M. & Keeper Veronica

Everyone knows that SkyPark has adventure attractions, a mountain bike park, summer concerts and a skate rink, but did you also know that we host weddings? And if you're engaged and looking for the perfect setting to celebrate your vows, we have the place for you. Join us for an Open House event at the breathtaking SkyPark Weddings venue on Sunday, October 1st from 10am-2pm! Get ready to be amazed by the enchanting beauty of our location. Whether you're dreaming of a fairytale wedding or a magical celebration, our venue has it all. Come and explore the stunning grounds, lush forest, and elegant event spaces.

At the Open House, you'll have the opportunity to meet our friendly staff who will be more than happy to answer all your questions and help you envision your perfect day. Take a leisurely stroll through the picturesque surroundings, and imagine exchanging vows in our stunning outdoor ceremony area. Discover the charm of our romantic outdoor reception terrace that can be transformed into your dream setting.

We can't wait to show you why SkyPark Weddings is the perfect place to create unforgettable memories. This event is free, but an RSVP is required to ensure availability for your tour: https://bit.ly/SkyParkWeddingsOpenHouse

We took a peak into Santa's House 🤫 and it looks like he's got our Christmas VIP ticket holders on the brain! The VIP Christmas Experience at Santa's Village takes the guesswork out of planning your trip with admission and activities included.⁠
⁠
What's Included?⁠:⁠
⁠
Christmas is our busiest time of the year. The VIP Christmas Experience allows you to minimize your wait times and maximize your time in the park.⁠
–⁠
When you arrive at Santa’s Village, you’ll already have your assigned entrance wristbands which will allow you to skip the main admission line. Parking is also included, so you don’t have to worry about paying an extra fee.⁠
–⁠
Your VIP Christmas Experience also includes a pre-assigned reservation time for a visit with Santa Claus, and your vouchers for cookie decorating and toy-making are sent along with your VIP gift box to streamline the process. You won’t have to fight the crowds for a space or wait in the standby line, simply arrive at Santa’s House at your scheduled time and one of Santa’s elves will escort you inside.⁠
⁠
Quantities are limited, so don’t wait - order your VIP Experience today!⁠
⁠
More info here: https://skyparksantasvillage.com/vip_christmas_experience_20

Tropical milkweed doesn't die back in California over the winter, which means Monarchs with access to it may stay too long before traveling to their overwintering grounds and and become more susceptible to the protozoan parasite Ophryocystis elektroscirrha, or OE for short. You can help protect Monarchs by cutting back Tropical milkweed in mid-October or planting milkweeds that are native to this area including: Narrow-Leaf Milkweed, showy milkweed, California, Heartleaf and Wooly Milkweeds #PlayitSAFE #SAFEMonarchs #FeedTheMigration #SavingSpecies #SAFEMonarchNetwork #MonarchConservation #MonarchButterfly #MoreThanMonarchs
